Venus is often called Cytherea by Virgil, from the
island Cythera, near which she rose from the sea, and where she
was worshipped with special veneration.  For the position of the
planet Venus in Pisces (the constellation preceding Aries or
dawn), see above, Canto i. 19-21, ^note.~
